						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/CGIAR-calls-for-commitment-to-funding-agricultural-research" title="CGIAR calls for commitment to funding agricultural research" alt="link">CGIAR calls for commitment to funding agricultural research</a></h2>

	
					<p> 
Consultative Group on International Agricultural Research (CGIAR) today called for renewed commitment to a revolution in sustainable agriculture, which was set for success in the 1990s but then stalled as a result of waning financial support. Emile Frison, Director General of Bioversity International – one of 15 centers supported by the CGIAR Centers said in Rome during the High-Level Conference on World Food Security that wealthy countries cut their support roughly in half from US$6 billion to $2.8 billion between 1980 and 2006 ostensibly adjusting for inflation and exchange rates within their countries. Success will require a substantial increase in funding and collective action among all key actors and players,” Frison stressed. We believe that, in order to deliver the knowledge and technologies required, we must double our annual investment in pro-poor research.” Source: Henry Neondo, African Science News Service, 4 June 2008.  </p>
							<p><span class="date">30/06/2008</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/CGIAR-calls-for-commitment-to-funding-agricultural-research">Read more...</a>
